headline: First Solar Beat the S&P 500 Last Year. Why the Stock Is Down 10% Today.
summary: First Solar  stock has seen healthy gains over the past year, surging 28% to outstrip the  17% gain.  Analysts led by Julien Dumoulin-Smith downgraded the stock to Hold from Buy in a note Wednesday.  The team also adjusted their price target slightly lower for First Solar to $260 from $269, citing limited upside potential for the maker of solar panels.
